HEADWORD: Clinkstone
<hw>Clink"stone`</hw> <pr>(?; 110)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Clink</ets> + <ets>stone</ets>; -- from its
sonorousness.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An igneous rock of
feldspathic composition, lamellar in structure, and clinking under the
hammer. See <er>Phonolite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clinodiagonal</ent>⟦br⟧
